tasks.description:
Apply the following style fixes in `pi-host-tui/src/tui/ui/chat.rs`:

1. **Line 270**: Change `pub(crate) fn build_status_spans` to `fn build_status_spans` (module-private suffices for tests)

2. **Lines 113, 130**: Change `///` doc comments to `//` comments for private helpers (consistent with file style)

3. **Lines 114-128**: Rewrite `format_tokens` from staircase `return` to `if/else if` chain:
```rust
fn format_tokens(count: u32) -> String {
    if count < 1000 {
        count.to_string()
    } else if count < 10_000 {
        format!("{:.1}k", count as f64 / 1000.0)
    } else if count < 1_000_000 {
        format!("{}k", (count as f64 / 1000.0).round() as u32)
    } else if count < 10_000_000 {
        format!("{:.1}M", count as f64 / 1_000_000.0)
    } else {
        format!("{}M", (count as f64 / 1_000_000.0).round() as u32)
    }
}
```

4. **Line 545**: Check how many times `span_text` is used. If ≤2 uses, inline it. If more, keep it but remove explicit lifetime annotation: `fn span_text(s: &Span<'static>) -> &str { s.content.as_ref() }`

Run `cargo test -p pi-host-tui` to verify all tests still pass.

Add two missing test cases in `pi-host-tui/src/tui/ui/chat.rs` in the `#[cfg(test)] mod tests` block:

1. **Test for pct > 100%**:
```rust
#[test]
fn format_ctx_usage_over_100_percent_is_red() {
    let (text, color) = format_ctx_usage(150_000, 128_000, true);
    assert!(text.contains("117.2%"));
    assert_eq!(color, Color::Red);
}
```

2. **Test for running + tasks combined**:
```rust
#[test]
fn build_status_spans_running_with_tasks_shows_tools_not_dot() {
    let mut app = app_with_agent();
    app.running = true;
    let (_tx, rx) = std::sync::mpsc::channel();
    app.running_tasks.push(crate::app::RunningTask {
        tool_call_id: pi_core::types::ToolCallId("tc1".to_string()),
        stream: Box::new(rx),
    });
    let spans = app.build_status_spans();
    // Should show tools indicator, not bare running dot
    assert_eq!(span_text(spans.last().unwrap()), " ● 1 tools");
    // Should NOT have a bare " ●" running indicator
    assert!(!spans.iter().any(|s| s.content.as_ref() == " ●"));
}
```

Run `cargo test -p pi-host-tui` to verify.
